From 56674ff9846617591cfe423143aa5cdae5d205dd Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: tlindell <tlindell@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 13 May 2026 10:44:09 -0500
Subject: [PATCH] Add CursorEdgeTeleport: warp cursor across unaligned outputs

Adds an opt-in cursor-warp behavior controlled by
[CursorEdgeTeleport]/Enabled in kwinrc. When enabled, motion that would
corner-pin the cursor in a dead zone (no adjacent output at the
cursors perpendicular coordinate) instead warps to the nearest
reachable point on an adjacent output in the motion direction.

When the flag is off (default), behavior is byte-identical to stock
KWin.

New modules:
  src/cursor_edge_teleport.{h,cpp}        Pure geometry algorithm
  src/cursor_edge_teleport_config.{h,cpp} kwinrc reader + KConfigWatcher
  autotests/test_cursor_edge_teleport.cpp 9 unit tests, 1ms runtime

Modified:
  src/pointer_input.cpp     Conditional block in updatePosition before
                            the existing confineToBoundingBox clamp;
                            CursorEdgeTeleportConfig::load() wired into
                            PointerInputRedirection::init()
  src/CMakeLists.txt        Registers new sources
  autotests/CMakeLists.txt  Registers testCursorEdgeTeleport target

Enable via:
  kwriteconfig6 --file kwinrc --group CursorEdgeTeleport --key Enabled true
  qdbus org.kde.KWin /KWin reconfigure
